<snippet>
	<content><![CDATA[const getScrollPosition = (el = window) => ({
  x: el.pageXOffset !== undefined ? el.pageXOffset : el.scrollLeft,
  y: el.pageYOffset !== undefined ? el.pageYOffset : el.scrollTop
});]]></content>
	<description>Returns the scroll position of the current page.  Use `pageXOffset` and `pageYOffset` if they are defined, otherwise `scrollLeft` and `scrollTop`. You can omit `el` to use a default value of `window`.</description>
	<tabTrigger>getScrollPosition</tabTrigger>
